  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Bureau of Labor Statistics U-3 unemployment rate. Monthly, 1st Friday 8:30 ET. Standard definition: persons without jobs who actively sought work in past 4 weeks.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Strong NFP bullish for equities except when economy at capacity (then rate-fear dominates). Unemployment below NAIRU (~4%) = Fed pressure. Rising unemployment = growth concern but also potential for Fed cuts.\n",
    "scoring_rule": "Score depends on direction vs Fed mandate. Rising + above 4.5% = bullish (cuts coming). Rising from low = early warning. Phase 3.\n"
  },
